<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="16">Integument lineated. P-2 ventral margin straight, distally forming a right angle; P-4 ventral setae at the same level.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="1" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="16">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="1" pageNumber="16">
General features: Integument lineated, occassionaly lines formed as irregular ridges (Fig. 2C). Posteromedial margin of Cx-I slightly triangular, Cx-IV medial margin nose-like protruding. Acetabula arranged in an obtuse triangle; excretory pore 
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="17" start="start">unsclerotized</pageBreakToken>
, distance genital field - excretory pore L in male 110-241, in female 280-351. Palp: P-2 ventral margin straight, distally forming a right angle, denticles covering two-thirds of the ventral margin of both P-2 and P-3; P-4 ventral setae on the same level.
</paragraph>
